 UDGs show signs of tidal\ndisruption and only two are tidal dwarf galaxy candidates. A study of globular\ncluster (GC) candidates selected in the CFHT images finds no evidence of a\nhigher GC specific frequency S_N for UDGs than for classical dwarfs, contrary\nto what is found in most clusters. The UDG halo-to-stellar mass ratio\ndistribution, as estimated from the GC counts, peaks at roughly the same value\nas for the traditional dwarfs, but spans the smaller range of ~10-2000. We\ninterpret these results to mean that the large majority of the field-to-group\nUDGs do not have a different formation scenario than traditional dwarfs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 Sep 2021 16:33:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-27"}
