 different regimes\nwith different radiative efficiencies: the thick disk and the slim disk. While\nthe existence of these two regimes is intrinsically linked to the JED-SAD\nmodel, we show direct observational evidence of the presence of two different\nregimes using the evolution of the X-ray power-law spectral index, a\nmodel-independent estimate. We then argue that these two regimes could be the\norigin of the gap in X-ray luminosity in the hard state, the wiggles and\ndifferent slopes seen in the radio--X-ray correlation, and even the existence\nof outliers.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Sep 2021 10:08:53 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 30 Sep 2021 09:21:02 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 11 Jan 2022 14:01:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-30"}
