ts a random first order\ntransition and compute the dynamical, condensation and Kesten-Stigum\ntransitions; we also compare the analytical predictions with Monte Carlo\nsimulations for values of $\\theta = 2\\pi/q$, $q \\in \\mathbb{N}$. Choosing such\nvalues of $q$ allows us to easily compare our results with the renowned problem\nof discrete coloring.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Sep 2021 12:04:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-11"}
